# ENCReload — PUBLIC repo. Version-control the mod data + OUR OWN code/config only.
# Hard rule: never commit copyrighted game content — the Amplitude/Humankind SDK
# (Assets/[Amplitude.*]) and the game's Resources/Editor framework must stay out.
# Large generated/baked output (Unity Library/Temp, built AssetBundles, Assets/Resources)
# also stays out (Assets/Resources is backed up separately on D:).

# Ignore everything at the project root by default...
/*

# ...except our own tracked trees.
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/AUTHORING.md
!/LICENSE
!/Assets
!/Tools
!/ProjectSettings
!/Packages
!/docs

# --- Assets: ignore every sibling, then re-include only OUR data + code ---
/Assets/*
!/Assets/Databases
!/Assets/Scripts
# The self-contained HAF pack (source of truth): pack.json + sounds/ + skins/, shipped as one directory.
# These are runtime FILE-assets (raw WAV/PNG read by the plugin), not Unity assets — keep their .meta out.
!/Assets/Pack
/Assets/Pack/**/*.meta

# --- Packages: only the dependency manifests, NOT the downloaded PackageCache ---
/Packages/*
!/Packages/manifest.json
!/Packages/packages-lock.json

# --- Tools: our Blender scripts + glbconv (source + self-contained exe), but not build junk ---
/Tools/glbconv/bin
/Tools/glbconv/obj
/Tools/**/__pycache__
